-- Cheung Kong, Sun Hung Kai Weekend Sales Top HK$11 Billion, SCMP Reports
-- B y   S t a n l e y   J a m e s
-- 2010-10-03T23:23:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-03/cheung-kong-sun-hung-kai-weekend-sales-top-hk-11-billion-scmp-reports.html
Cheung Kong Holdings Ltd. and Sun
Hung Kai Properties Ltd. sold HK$11 billion worth of property
over the long weekend, the South China Morning Post reported.  Cheung Kong, which was offering apartments at its Oceanaire
project in Ma on Shan for an average of HK$6,500 a square foot,
said sales for the four days exceeded HK$7 billion, while Sun
Hung Kai said the first batch of 132 homes at its Valais complex
in Sheung Shui were almost sold out, bringing in more than HK$4
billion, according to the Morning Post.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stanley James at 
 sjames8@bloomberg.net  